### Instructions to Host on GitHub Pages

1. **Create a GitHub Repository:**
   - Go to [GitHub](https://github.com/) and sign in.
   - Click the `+` icon in the upper right corner and select `New repository`.
   - Name your repository (e.g., `my-website`) and set it to public.
   - Click `Create repository`.

2. **Upload Your HTML File:**
   - In your new repository, click on `Add file` and select `Upload files`.
   - Drag and drop your `index.html` file or click to select the file from your computer.
   - Commit the changes by clicking `Commit changes` at the bottom of the page.

3. **Enable GitHub Pages:**
   - Go to the `Settings` tab of your repository.
   - Scroll down to the `GitHub Pages` section.
   - Under `Source`, select the branch you want to use (e.g., `main` or `master`).
   - Click `Save`.

4. **Access Your Website:**
   - After a few moments, your site should be available at `https://<your-username>.github.io/<repository-name>/`.

For example, if your username is `waliullah` and your repository is `my-website`, the URL will be `https://waliullah.github.io/my-website/`.
